Certainly! To compare the trade protectionism level of France and Germany over the past decade, we'll need to analyze the trade balance, exports, and imports data for each country. This analysis will involve loading the data into MATLAB, performing trend analysis, and plotting the results to identify any patterns or changes in their trade policies.

Here’s a step-by-step MATLAB code example for such an analysis. Note that this is a template, and you will need to replace the placeholders with actual data.

```matlab
% Load data
% Assuming data is in the format: Year, France_Exports, France_Imports, Germany_Exports, Germany_Imports
data = [
    2013, 500, 550, 800, 830;  % Example data
    2014, 520, 560, 820, 840;
    2015, 530, 570, 840, 860;
    2016, 540, 580, 850, 870;
    2017, 550, 590, 860, 880;
    2018, 560, 600, 870, 890;
    2019, 570, 610, 880, 900;
    2020, 580, 620, 890, 910;
    2021, 590, 630, 900, 920;
    2022, 600, 640, 910, 930
];

years = data(:, 1);
france_exports = data(:, 2);
france_imports = data(:, 3);
germany_exports = data(:, 4);
germany_imports = data(:, 5);

% Calculate Trade Balance
france_trade_balance = france_exports - france_imports;
germany_trade_balance = germany_exports - germany_imports;

% Plot Exports, Imports, and Trade Balance
figure;

subplot(3, 1, 1);
plot(years, france_exports, '-o', 'DisplayName', 'France Exports');
hold on;
plot(years, france_imports, '-o', 'DisplayName', 'France Imports');
title('France Exports and Imports');
xlabel('Year');
ylabel('Value (in million $)');
legend show;
grid on;

subplot(3, 1, 2);
plot(years, germany_exports, '-o', 'DisplayName', 'Germany Exports');
hold on;
plot(years, germany_imports, '-o', 'DisplayName', 'Germany Imports');
title('Germany Exports and Imports');
xlabel('Year');
ylabel('Value (in million $)');
legend show;
grid on;

subplot(3, 1, 3);
plot(years, france_trade_balance, '-o', 'DisplayName', 'France Trade Balance');
hold on;
plot(years, germany_trade_balance, '-o', 'DisplayName', 'Germany Trade Balance');
title('Trade Balance Comparison');
xlabel('Year');
ylabel('Trade Balance (in million $)');
legend show;
grid on;

% Trend Analysis
france_trend = polyfit(years, france_trade_balance, 1);
germany_trend = polyfit(years, germany_trade_balance, 1);

france_fit = polyval(france_trend, years);
germany_fit = polyval(germany_trend, years);

figure;
plot(years, france_trade_balance, '-o', 'DisplayName', 'France Trade Balance');
hold on;
plot(years, germany_trade_balance, '-o', 'DisplayName', 'Germany Trade Balance');
plot(years, france_fit, '--', 'DisplayName', 'France Trend');
plot(years, germany_fit, '--', 'DisplayName', 'Germany Trend');
title('Trade Balance Trend Analysis');
xlabel('Year');
ylabel('Trade Balance (in million $)');
legend show;
grid on;

% Conclusion
fprintf('France Trade Balance Trend: %.2f\n', france_trend(1));
fprintf('Germany Trade Balance Trend: %.2f\n', germany_trend(1));

if france_trend(1) > germany_trend(1)
    fprintf('France shows a greater increase in trade balance over the past decade, indicating less protectionism compared to Germany.\n');
elseif france_trend(1) < germany_trend(1)
    fprintf('Germany shows a greater increase in trade balance over the past decade, indicating less protectionism compared to France.\n');
else
    fprintf('Both countries show similar trends in trade balance, indicating comparable levels of protectionism.\n');
end
```

### Explanation:
- **Data Loading**: Replace the example data with actual trade data for France and Germany.
- **Trade Balance Calculation**: The trade balance is calculated as exports minus imports.
- **Plotting**: Exports, imports, and trade balance are plotted to visually assess trends.
- **Trend Analysis**: Linear trends are calculated using polynomial fitting.
- **Conclusion**: Based on the trend slopes, we infer the relative protectionism level.

This analysis assumes that a positive trend in the trade balance suggests decreasing protectionism, as it indicates an increasing surplus or decreasing deficit. Adjust the analysis based on more specific policy considerations if necessary.
